               Kruskal-Wallis test) were used to analyze the data. 68.3\% of
               nurses, were female, with a mean age of 29.4 + 4.9 years and
               66.7\% had no prior information about the Braden Scale. The
               overall mean scores change of the pre-to-post educational
               intervention for knowledge and attitude was statistically
               significant, p",
  journal   = "SAGE Open",
  publisher = "SAGE Publications",
  volume    =  15,
  number    =  2,
  month     =  apr,
  year      =  2025,
  language  = "en"
}

